text: Kyyjärvi is a municipality in Central Finland. About 1,430 people lived there in January 2014. The municipalities next to it are Alajärvi, Karstula, Kivijärvi, Perho and Soini. There is also a lake called Kyyjärvi what is located in the Kyyjärvi municipality. The name Kyyjärvi means "adder lake" in Finnish. Kyyjärvi was established in 1929. ==Distances== * Jyväskylä 115 km * Vaasa 160 km * Seinäjoki 110 km == Other websites == * The official page Category:Municipalities of Central Finland Category:1929 establishments in Europe Category:1920s establishments in Finland
